{
  "video_id": "w8lH8tNlAXc",
  "title": "What will humans look like in 100 years? | Juan Enriquez",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 14760.0,
      "end_time": 16280.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s a question that matters."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16880.0,
      "end_time": 18855.0,
      "text": "[Is it ethical to evolve the human body?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18880.0,
      "end_time": 22375.0,
      "text": "Because we&#39;re beginning to get all the tools together to evolve ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22400.0,
      "end_time": 24816.0,
      "text": "And we can evolve bacteria and we can evolve plants"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24840.0,
      "end_time": 26256.0,
      "text": "and we can evolve animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26280.0,
      "end_time": 29960.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re now reaching a point where we really have to ask,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29120.0,
      "end_time": 31960.0,
      "text": "is it really ethical and do we want to evolve human beings?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33440.0,
      "end_time": 35336.0,
      "text": "And as you&#39;re thinking about that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35360.0,
      "end_time": 39960.0,
      "text": "let me talk about that in the context of prosthetics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39120.0,
      "end_time": 41800.0,
      "text": "prosthetics past, present, future."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42920.0,
      "end_time": 44496.0,
      "text": "So this is the iron hand"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44520.0,
      "end_time": 46856.0,
      "text": "that belonged to one of the German counts."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 46880.0,
      "end_time": 51296.0,
      "text": "Loved to fight, lost his arm in one of these battles."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51320.0,
      "end_time": 53776.0,
      "text": "No problem, he just made a suit of armor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 53800.0,
      "end_time": 55135.0,
      "text": "put it on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55160.0,
      "end_time": 56416.0,
      "text": "perfect prosthetic."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56440.0,
      "end_time": 60360.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s where the concept of ruling with an iron fist comes from."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61600.0,
      "end_time": 65560.0,
      "text": "And of course these prosthetics have been getting more and more useful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 65800.0,
      "end_time": 66336.0,
      "text": "more and more modern."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 66360.0,
      "end_time": 68816.0,
      "text": "You can hold soft-boiled eggs."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 68840.0,
      "end_time": 72336.0,
      "text": "You can have all types of controls, and as you&#39;re thinking about that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 72360.0,
      "end_time": 74376.0,
      "text": "there are wonderful people like Hugh Herr"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 74400.0,
      "end_time": 77239.0,
      "text": "who have been building absolutely extraordinary prosthetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77720.0,
      "end_time": 80536.0,
      "text": "So the wonderful Aimee Mullins will go out and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 80560.0,
      "end_time": 82240.0,
      "text": "how tall do I want to be tonight?"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83400.0,
      "end_time": 85936.0,
      "text": "Or Hugh will say what type of cliff do I want to climb?"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 85960.0,
      "end_time": 90455.0,
      "text": "Or does somebody want to run a marathon, or does somebody want to ballroom dance?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90480.0,
      "end_time": 92456.0,
      "text": "And as you adapt these things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92480.0,
      "end_time": 96616.0,
      "text": "the interesting thing about prosthetics is they&#39;ve been coming inside the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96640.0,
      "end_time": 99616.0,
      "text": "So these external prosthetics have now become artificial knees."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99640.0,
      "end_time": 101696.0,
      "text": "They&#39;ve become artificial hips."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 101720.0,
      "end_time": 103936.0,
      "text": "And then they&#39;ve evolved further"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 103960.0,
      "end_time": 105976.0,
      "text": "to become not just nice to have"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 106000.0,
      "end_time": 107200.0,
      "text": "but essential to have."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107920.0,
      "end_time": 111776.0,
      "text": "So when you&#39;re talking about a heart pacemaker as a prosthetic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111800.0,
      "end_time": 115496.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re talking about something that isn&#39;t just, \"I&#39;m missing my leg,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 115520.0,
      "end_time": 117936.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s, \"if I don&#39;t have this, I can die.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117960.0,
      "end_time": 122560.0,
      "text": "And at that point, a prosthetic becomes a symbiotic relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 122800.0,
      "end_time": 123280.0,
      "text": "with the human body."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 124560.0,
      "end_time": 127960.0,
      "text": "And four of the smartest people that I&#39;ve ever met --"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127120.0,
      "end_time": 132376.0,
      "text": "Ed Boyden, Hugh Herr, Joe Jacobson, Bob Lander --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132400.0,
      "end_time": 134976.0,
      "text": "are working on a Center for Extreme Bionics."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135000.0,
      "end_time": 137616.0,
      "text": "And the interesting thing of what you&#39;re seeing here is"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 137640.0,
      "end_time": 140550.0,
      "text": "these prosthetics now get integrated into the bone."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 140800.0,
      "end_time": 141735.0,
      "text": "They get integrated into the skin."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 141759.0,
      "end_time": 143475.0,
      "text": "They get integrated into the muscle."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 144360.0,
      "end_time": 147336.0,
      "text": "And one of the other sides of Ed"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 147360.0,
      "end_time": 150256.0,
      "text": "is he&#39;s been thinking about how to connect the brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 150280.0,
      "end_time": 152976.0,
      "text": "using light or other mechanisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 153000.0,
      "end_time": 155280.0,
      "text": "directly to things like these prosthetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 156520.0,
      "end_time": 157776.0,
      "text": "And if you can do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 157800.0,
      "end_time": 161000.0,
      "text": "then you can begin changing fundamental aspects of humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 161840.0,
      "end_time": 165840.0,
      "text": "So how quickly you react to something depends on the diameter of a nerve."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 166920.0,
      "end_time": 170799.0,
      "text": "And of course, if you have nerves that are external or prosthetic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171600.0,
      "end_time": 173480.0,
      "text": "say with light or liquid metal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 174280.0,
      "end_time": 175976.0,
      "text": "then you can increase that diameter"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176000.0,
      "end_time": 179560.0,
      "text": "and you could even increase it theoretically to the point where,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 179800.0,
      "end_time": 183120.0,
      "text": "as long as you could see the muzzle flash, you could step out of the way of a bullet."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 183840.0,
      "end_time": 186960.0,
      "text": "Those are the order of magnitude of changes you&#39;re talking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 188200.0,
      "end_time": 190775.0,
      "text": "This is a fourth sort of level of prosthetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 190800.0,
      "end_time": 193336.0,
      "text": "These are Phonak hearing aids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 193360.0,
      "end_time": 195416.0,
      "text": "and the reason why these are so interesting"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 195440.0,
      "end_time": 198856.0,
      "text": "is because they cross the threshold from where prosthetics are something"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 198880.0,
      "end_time": 200309.0,
      "text": "for somebody who is \"disabled\""
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 201560.0,
      "end_time": 205616.0,
      "text": "and they become something that somebody who is \"normal\""
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 205640.0,
      "end_time": 207535.0,
      "text": "might want to actually have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 207560.0,
      "end_time": 210536.0,
      "text": "because what this prosthetic does, which is really interesting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 210560.0,
      "end_time": 212216.0,
      "text": "is not only does it help you hear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212240.0,
      "end_time": 213576.0,
      "text": "you can focus your hearing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 213600.0,
      "end_time": 216550.0,
      "text": "so it can hear the conversation going on over there."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 216800.0,
      "end_time": 217336.0,
      "text": "You can have superhearing."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 217360.0,
      "end_time": 220296.0,
      "text": "You can have hearing in 360 degrees. You can have white noise."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220320.0,
      "end_time": 223519.0,
      "text": "You can record, and oh, by the way, they also put a phone into this."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224440.0,
      "end_time": 227320.0,
      "text": "So this functions as your hearing aid and also as your phone."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 227920.0,
      "end_time": 233790.0,
      "text": "And at that point, somebody might actually want to have a prosthetic voluntarily."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 234400.0,
      "end_time": 237960.0,
      "text": "All of these thousands of loosely connected little pieces"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 237120.0,
      "end_time": 238320.0,
      "text": "are coming together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 239120.0,
      "end_time": 241560.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s about time we ask the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 241800.0,
      "end_time": 244240.0,
      "text": "how do we want to evolve human beings over the next century or two?"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 245640.0,
      "end_time": 247679.0,
      "text": "And for that we turn to a great philosopher"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 248920.0,
      "end_time": 251976.0,
      "text": "who was a very smart man despite being a Yankee fan."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 252000.0,
      "end_time": 253880.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 254800.0,
      "end_time": 258616.0,
      "text": "And Yogi Berra used to say, of course, that it&#39;s very tough to make predictions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 258640.0,
      "end_time": 260150.0,
      "text": "especially about the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 260399.99999999997,
      "end_time": 261135.99999999997,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 261160.00000000003,
      "end_time": 264216.0,
      "text": "So instead of making a prediction about the future to begin with,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 264240.0,
      "end_time": 267576.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s take what&#39;s happening in the present with people like Tony Atala,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 267600.0,
      "end_time": 269839.0,
      "text": "who is redesigning 30-some-odd organs."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 271200.0,
      "end_time": 274776.0,
      "text": "And maybe the ultimate prosthetic isn&#39;t having something external, titanium."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 274800.0,
      "end_time": 277496.0,
      "text": "Maybe the ultimate prosthetic is take your own gene code,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 277520.0,
      "end_time": 278840.0,
      "text": "remake your own body parts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 279920.0,
      "end_time": 283520.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s a whole lot more effective than any kind of a prosthetic."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 284440.0,
      "end_time": 288456.0,
      "text": "But while you&#39;re at it, then you can take the work of Craig Venter and Ham Smith."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 288480.0,
      "end_time": 290536.0,
      "text": "And one of the things that we&#39;ve been doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 290560.0,
      "end_time": 293120.0,
      "text": "is trying to figure out how to reprogram cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 294280.0,
      "end_time": 295856.0,
      "text": "And if you can reprogram a cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 295880.0,
      "end_time": 298120.0,
      "text": "then you can change the cells in those organs."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 299400.0,
      "end_time": 301616.0,
      "text": "So if you can change the cells in those organs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 301640.0,
      "end_time": 304135.0,
      "text": "maybe you make those organs more radiation-resistant."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 304160.0,
      "end_time": 306560.0,
      "text": "Maybe you make them absorb more oxygen."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 306800.0,
      "end_time": 307736.0,
      "text": "Maybe you make them more efficient"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 307760.0,
      "end_time": 310240.0,
      "text": "to filter out stuff that you don&#39;t want in your body."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 311440.0,
      "end_time": 315960.0,
      "text": "And over the last few weeks, George Church has been in the news a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 315120.0,
      "end_time": 318416.0,
      "text": "because he&#39;s been talking about taking one of these programmable cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 318440.0,
      "end_time": 320176.0,
      "text": "and inserting an entire human genome"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 320200.0,
      "end_time": 321400.0,
      "text": "into that cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 322480.0,
      "end_time": 326296.0,
      "text": "And once you can insert an entire human genome into a cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 326320.0,
      "end_time": 328456.0,
      "text": "then you begin to ask the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 328480.0,
      "end_time": 331160.0,
      "text": "would you want to enhance any of that genome?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 333440.0,
      "end_time": 335776.0,
      "text": "Do you want to enhance a human body?"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 335800.0,
      "end_time": 338960.0,
      "text": "How would you want to enhance a human body?"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 338120.0,
      "end_time": 340216.0,
      "text": "Where is it ethical to enhance a human body"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 340240.0,
      "end_time": 343496.0,
      "text": "and where is it not ethical to enhance a human body?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 343520.0,
      "end_time": 345416.0,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, what we&#39;re doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 345440.0,
      "end_time": 348376.0,
      "text": "is we&#39;ve got this multidimensional chess board"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 348400.0,
      "end_time": 351655.0,
      "text": "where we can change human genetics by using viruses"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 351680.0,
      "end_time": 353120.0,
      "text": "to attack things like AIDS,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 354120.0,
      "end_time": 356536.0,
      "text": "or we can change the gene code through gene therapy"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 356560.0,
      "end_time": 359496.0,
      "text": "to do away with some hereditary diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 359520.0,
      "end_time": 361135.0,
      "text": "or we can change the environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 361160.0,
      "end_time": 363827.0,
      "text": "and change the expression of those genes in the epigenome"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 363851.0,
      "end_time": 365811.0,
      "text": "and pass that on to the next generations."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 367320.0,
      "end_time": 370456.0,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, it&#39;s not just one little bit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 370480.0,
      "end_time": 372336.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s all these stacked little bits"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 372360.0,
      "end_time": 374440.0,
      "text": "that allow you to take little portions of it"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 375280.0,
      "end_time": 377280.0,
      "text": "until all the portions coming together"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 378160.0,
      "end_time": 380240.0,
      "text": "lead you to something that&#39;s very different."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 381600.0,
      "end_time": 384336.0,
      "text": "And a lot of people are very scared by this stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 384360.0,
      "end_time": 387280.0,
      "text": "And it does sound scary, and there are risks to this stuff."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 388400.0,
      "end_time": 390736.0,
      "text": "So why in the world would you ever want to do this stuff?"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 390760.0,
      "end_time": 393776.0,
      "text": "Why would we really want to alter the human body"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 393800.0,
      "end_time": 395000.0,
      "text": "in a fundamental way?"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 397400.0,
      "end_time": 399336.0,
      "text": "The answer lies in part"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 399360.0,
      "end_time": 400560.0,
      "text": "with Lord Rees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 401240.0,
      "end_time": 402920.0,
      "text": "astronomer royal of Great Britain."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 404560.0,
      "end_time": 408376.0,
      "text": "And one of his favorite sayings is the universe is 100 percent malevolent."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 408400.0,
      "end_time": 409616.0,
      "text": "So what does that mean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 409640.0,
      "end_time": 412536.0,
      "text": "It means if you take any one of your bodies at random,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 412560.0,
      "end_time": 414456.0,
      "text": "drop it anywhere in the universe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 414480.0,
      "end_time": 416200.0,
      "text": "drop it in space, you die."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 416720.0,
      "end_time": 418960.0,
      "text": "Drop it on the Sun, you die."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 418120.0,
      "end_time": 420136.0,
      "text": "Drop it on the surface of Mercury, you die."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 420160.0,
      "end_time": 421800.0,
      "text": "Drop it near a supernova, you die."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 422240.0,
      "end_time": 425360.0,
      "text": "But fortunately, it&#39;s only about 80 percent effective."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 426640.0,
      "end_time": 428680.0,
      "text": "So as a great physicist once said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 430000.0,
      "end_time": 434136.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s these little upstream eddies of biology"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 434160.0,
      "end_time": 438800.0,
      "text": "that create order in this rapid torrent of entropy."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 440800.0,
      "end_time": 443560.0,
      "text": "So as the universe dissipates energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 443800.0,
      "end_time": 446560.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s these upstream eddies that create biological order."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 447960.0,
      "end_time": 450376.0,
      "text": "Now, the problem with eddies is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 450400.0,
      "end_time": 451895.0,
      "text": "they tend to disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 451920.0,
      "end_time": 453800.0,
      "text": "They shift. They move in rivers."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 454680.0,
      "end_time": 456656.0,
      "text": "And because of that, when an eddy shifts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 456680.0,
      "end_time": 460216.0,
      "text": "when the Earth becomes a snowball, when the Earth becomes very hot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 460240.0,
      "end_time": 463496.0,
      "text": "when the Earth gets hit by an asteroid, when you have supervolcanoes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 463520.0,
      "end_time": 465376.0,
      "text": "when you have solar flares,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 465400.0,
      "end_time": 468736.0,
      "text": "when you have potentially extinction-level events"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 468760.0,
      "end_time": 469976.0,
      "text": "like the next election --"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 470000.0,
      "end_time": 472160.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 473440.0,
      "end_time": 476680.0,
      "text": "then all of a sudden, you can have periodic extinctions."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 477400.0,
      "end_time": 479840.0,
      "text": "And by the way, that&#39;s happened five times on Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 480360.0,
      "end_time": 482456.0,
      "text": "and therefore it is very likely"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 482480.0,
      "end_time": 485520.0,
      "text": "that the human species on Earth is going to go extinct someday."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 486440.0,
      "end_time": 487936.0,
      "text": "Not next week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 487960.0,
      "end_time": 489775.0,
      "text": "not next month,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 489800.0,
      "end_time": 492680.0,
      "text": "maybe in November, but maybe 10,000 years after that."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 493880.0,
      "end_time": 496695.0,
      "text": "As you&#39;re thinking of the consequence of that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 496720.0,
      "end_time": 500136.0,
      "text": "if you believe that extinctions are common and natural"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 500160.0,
      "end_time": 502456.0,
      "text": "and normal and occur periodically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 502480.0,
      "end_time": 505360.0,
      "text": "it becomes a moral imperative to diversify our species."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 506520.0,
      "end_time": 508135.0,
      "text": "And it becomes a moral imperative"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 508160.0,
      "end_time": 511136.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s going to be really hard to live on Mars"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 511160.0,
      "end_time": 513880.0,
      "text": "if we don&#39;t fundamentally modify the human body."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 514880.0,
      "end_time": 516960.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 516120.0,
      "end_time": 517456.0,
      "text": "You go from one cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 517480.0,
      "end_time": 519696.0,
      "text": "mom and dad coming together to make one cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 519720.0,
      "end_time": 521896.0,
      "text": "in a cascade to 10 trillion cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 521919.0,
      "end_time": 526376.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t know, if you change the gravity substantially,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 526400.0,
      "end_time": 528880.0,
      "text": "if the same thing will happen to create your body."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 530159.0,
      "end_time": 533216.0,
      "text": "We do know that if you expose our bodies as they currently are"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 533240.0,
      "end_time": 535360.0,
      "text": "to a lot of radiation, we will die."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 537400.0,
      "end_time": 540960.0,
      "text": "So as you&#39;re thinking of that, you have to really redesign things"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 540120.0,
      "end_time": 541376.0,
      "text": "just to get to Mars."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 541400.0,
      "end_time": 544319.0,
      "text": "Forget about the moons of Neptune or Jupiter."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 545000.0,
      "end_time": 547456.0,
      "text": "And to borrow from Nikolai Kardashev,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 547480.0,
      "end_time": 549656.0,
      "text": "let&#39;s think about life in a series of scales."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 549680.0,
      "end_time": 552175.0,
      "text": "So Life One civilization"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 552200.0,
      "end_time": 555200.0,
      "text": "is a civilization that begins to alter his or her looks."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 556800.0,
      "end_time": 558376.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve been doing that for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 558400.0,
      "end_time": 561560.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ve got tummy tucks and you&#39;ve got this and you&#39;ve got that."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 562280.0,
      "end_time": 564696.0,
      "text": "You alter your looks, and I&#39;m told"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 564720.0,
      "end_time": 568400.0,
      "text": "that not all of those alterations take place for medical reasons."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 568680.0,
      "end_time": 570736.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 570760.0,
      "end_time": 571960.0,
      "text": "Seems odd."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 572360.0,
      "end_time": 574880.0,
      "text": "A Life Two civilization is a different civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 576320.0,
      "end_time": 580880.0,
      "text": "A Life Two civilization alters fundamental aspects of the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 581840.0,
      "end_time": 584696.0,
      "text": "So you put human growth hormone in, the person grows taller,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 584720.0,
      "end_time": 588656.0,
      "text": "or you put x in and the person gets fatter or loses metabolism"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 588680.0,
      "end_time": 590295.0,
      "text": "or does a whole series of things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 590320.0,
      "end_time": 593160.0,
      "text": "but you&#39;re altering the functions in a fundamental way."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 593400.0,
      "end_time": 595656.0,
      "text": "To become an intrasolar civilization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 595680.0,
      "end_time": 598400.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to have to create a Life Three civilization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 599720.0,
      "end_time": 602320.0,
      "text": "and that looks very different from what we&#39;ve got here."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 602840.0,
      "end_time": 605560.0,
      "text": "Maybe you splice in Deinococcus radiodurans"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 605800.0,
      "end_time": 609200.0,
      "text": "so that the cells can resplice after a lot of exposure to radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 610320.0,
      "end_time": 613336.0,
      "text": "Maybe you breathe by having oxygen flow through your blood"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 613360.0,
      "end_time": 614800.0,
      "text": "instead of through your lungs."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 615600.0,
      "end_time": 618320.0,
      "text": "But you&#39;re talking about really radical redesigns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 619480.0,
      "end_time": 622696.0,
      "text": "and one of the interesting things that&#39;s happened in the last decade"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 622720.0,
      "end_time": 625456.0,
      "text": "is we&#39;ve discovered a whole lot of planets out there."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 625480.0,
      "end_time": 627160.0,
      "text": "And some of them may be Earth-like."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 629440.0,
      "end_time": 633560.0,
      "text": "The problem is, if we ever want to get to these planets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 633800.0,
      "end_time": 634736.0,
      "text": "the fastest human objects --"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 634760.0,
      "end_time": 637336.0,
      "text": "Juno and Voyager and the rest of this stuff --"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 637360.0,
      "end_time": 639856.0,
      "text": "take tens of thousands of years"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 639880.0,
      "end_time": 642000.0,
      "text": "to get from here to the nearest solar system."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 642720.0,
      "end_time": 645680.0,
      "text": "So if you want to start exploring beaches somewhere else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 646400.0,
      "end_time": 648800.0,
      "text": "or you want to see two-sun sunsets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 649840.0,
      "end_time": 652976.0,
      "text": "then you&#39;re talking about something that is very different,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 653000.0,
      "end_time": 658560.0,
      "text": "because you have to change the timescale and the body of humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 658800.0,
      "end_time": 661000.0,
      "text": "in ways which may be absolutely unrecognizable."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 662000.0,
      "end_time": 663840.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s a Life Four civilization."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 665720.0,
      "end_time": 668656.0,
      "text": "Now, we can&#39;t even begin to imagine what that might look like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 668680.0,
      "end_time": 671160.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;re beginning to get glimpses"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 671400.0,
      "end_time": 674400.0,
      "text": "of instruments that might take us even that far."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 674960.0,
      "end_time": 676576.0,
      "text": "And let me give you two examples."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 676600.0,
      "end_time": 678553.0,
      "text": "So this is the wonderful Floyd Romesberg,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 679200.0,
      "end_time": 681336.0,
      "text": "and one of the things that Floyd&#39;s been doing"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 681360.0,
      "end_time": 683896.0,
      "text": "is he&#39;s been playing with the basic chemistry of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 683920.0,
      "end_time": 688776.0,
      "text": "So all life on this planet is made in ATCGs, the four letters of DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 688800.0,
      "end_time": 691935.0,
      "text": "All bacteria, all plants, all animals, all humans, all cows,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 691960.0,
      "end_time": 693160.0,
      "text": "everything else."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 694440.0,
      "end_time": 698616.0,
      "text": "And what Floyd did is he changed out two of those base pairs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 698640.0,
      "end_time": 700160.0,
      "text": "so it&#39;s ATXY."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 701760.0,
      "end_time": 707456.0,
      "text": "And that means that you now have a parallel system to make life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 707480.0,
      "end_time": 711776.0,
      "text": "to make babies, to reproduce, to evolve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 711800.0,
      "end_time": 713976.0,
      "text": "that doesn&#39;t mate with most things on Earth"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 714000.0,
      "end_time": 715880.0,
      "text": "or in fact maybe with nothing on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 716880.0,
      "end_time": 719415.0,
      "text": "Maybe you make plants that are immune to all bacteria."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 719440.0,
      "end_time": 721936.0,
      "text": "Maybe you make plants that are immune to all viruses."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 721960.0,
      "end_time": 723496.0,
      "text": "But why is that so interesting?"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 723520.0,
      "end_time": 726680.0,
      "text": "It means that we are not a unique solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 727400.0,
      "end_time": 731136.0,
      "text": "It means you can create alternate chemistries to us"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 731160.0,
      "end_time": 735976.0,
      "text": "that could be chemistries adaptable to a very different planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 736000.0,
      "end_time": 738360.0,
      "text": "that could create life and heredity."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 740120.0,
      "end_time": 741360.0,
      "text": "The second experiment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 742480.0,
      "end_time": 744560.0,
      "text": "or the other implication of this experiment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 745360.0,
      "end_time": 749576.0,
      "text": "is that all of you, all life is based on 20 amino acids."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 749600.0,
      "end_time": 752560.0,
      "text": "If you don&#39;t substitute two amino acids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 752800.0,
      "end_time": 757656.0,
      "text": "if you don&#39;t say ATXY, if you say ATCG + XY,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 757680.0,
      "end_time": 760439.0,
      "text": "then you go from 20 building blocks to 172,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 761520.0,
      "end_time": 764656.0,
      "text": "and all of a sudden you&#39;ve got 172 building blocks of amino acids"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 764680.0,
      "end_time": 767479.0,
      "text": "to build life-forms in very different shapes."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 769480.0,
      "end_time": 772536.0,
      "text": "The second experiment to think about is a really weird experiment"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 772560.0,
      "end_time": 774640.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s been taking place in China."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 775920.0,
      "end_time": 779959.0,
      "text": "So this guy has been transplanting hundreds of mouse heads."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 780920.0,
      "end_time": 782295.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 782320.0,
      "end_time": 784400.0,
      "text": "And why is that an interesting experiment?"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 785440.0,
      "end_time": 787496.0,
      "text": "Well, think of the first heart transplants."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 787520.0,
      "end_time": 789136.0,
      "text": "One of the things they used to do"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 789160.0,
      "end_time": 792695.0,
      "text": "is they used to bring in the wife or the daughter of the donor"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 792720.0,
      "end_time": 796616.0,
      "text": "so the donee could tell the doctors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 796640.0,
      "end_time": 799256.0,
      "text": "\"Do you recognize this person? Do you love this person?"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 799280.0,
      "end_time": 801136.0,
      "text": "Do you feel anything for this person?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 801160.0,
      "end_time": 802640.0,
      "text": "We laugh about that today."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 803560.0,
      "end_time": 805776.0,
      "text": "We laugh because we know the heart is a muscle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 805800.0,
      "end_time": 809295.0,
      "text": "but for hundreds of thousands of years, or tens of thousands of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 809320.0,
      "end_time": 812216.0,
      "text": "\"I gave her my heart. She took my heart. She broke my heart.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 812240.0,
      "end_time": 813616.0,
      "text": "We thought this was emotion"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 813640.0,
      "end_time": 816880.0,
      "text": "and we thought maybe emotions were transplanted with the heart. Nope."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 818000.0,
      "end_time": 819480.0,
      "text": "So how about the brain?"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 821400.0,
      "end_time": 823120.0,
      "text": "Two possible outcomes to this experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 823880.0,
      "end_time": 826296.0,
      "text": "If you can get a mouse"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 826320.0,
      "end_time": 827936.0,
      "text": "that is functional,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 827960.0,
      "end_time": 829160.0,
      "text": "then you can see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 830400.0,
      "end_time": 831640.0,
      "text": "is the new brain a blank slate?"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 833280.0,
      "end_time": 835319.0,
      "text": "And boy, does that have implications."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 837120.0,
      "end_time": 838320.0,
      "text": "Second option:"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 838800.0,
      "end_time": 840920.0,
      "text": "the new mouse recognizes Minnie Mouse."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 841760.0,
      "end_time": 843856.0,
      "text": "The new mouse remembers what it&#39;s afraid of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 843880.0,
      "end_time": 845576.0,
      "text": "remembers how to navigate the maze,"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 845600.0,
      "end_time": 846800.0,
      "text": "and if that is true,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 848400.0,
      "end_time": 851360.0,
      "text": "then you can transplant memory and consciousness."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 853800.0,
      "end_time": 855496.0,
      "text": "And then the really interesting question is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 855520.0,
      "end_time": 859456.0,
      "text": "if you can transplant this, is the only input-output mechanism"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 859480.0,
      "end_time": 860680.0,
      "text": "this down here?"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 861440.0,
      "end_time": 864136.0,
      "text": "Or could you transplant that consciousness into something"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 864160.0,
      "end_time": 866136.0,
      "text": "that would be very different,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 866160.0,
      "end_time": 867415.0,
      "text": "that would last in space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 867440.0,
      "end_time": 869496.0,
      "text": "that would last tens of thousands of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 869520.0,
      "end_time": 871520.0,
      "text": "that would be a completely redesigned body"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 871544.0,
      "end_time": 875223.0,
      "text": "that could hold consciousness for a long, long period of time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 878400.0,
      "end_time": 880790.0,
      "text": "And let&#39;s come back to the first question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 880560.0,
      "end_time": 882439.0,
      "text": "Why would you ever want to do that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 884320.0,
      "end_time": 885576.0,
      "text": "Well, I&#39;ll tell you why."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 885600.0,
      "end_time": 887320.0,
      "text": "Because this is the ultimate selfie."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 888000.0,
      "end_time": 889800.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 890440.0,
      "end_time": 893000.0,
      "text": "This is taken from six billion miles away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 894400.0,
      "end_time": 895240.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 896800.0,
      "end_time": 898000.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s all of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 899240.0,
      "end_time": 902760.0,
      "text": "And if that little thing goes, all of humanity goes."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 904320.0,
      "end_time": 906536.0,
      "text": "And the reason you want to alter the human body"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 906560.0,
      "end_time": 909335.0,
      "text": "is because you eventually want a picture that says,"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 909360.0,
      "end_time": 911296.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s us, and that&#39;s us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 911320.0,
      "end_time": 912736.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 912760.0,
      "end_time": 915880.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s the way humanity survives long-term extinction."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 917440.0,
      "end_time": 919696.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s the reason why it turns out"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 919720.0,
      "end_time": 923656.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s actually unethical not to evolve the human body"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 923680.0,
      "end_time": 927160.0,
      "text": "even though it can be scary, even though it can be challenging,"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 927400.0,
      "end_time": 930415.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s what&#39;s going to allow us to explore, live"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 930440.0,
      "end_time": 932960.0,
      "text": "and get to places we can&#39;t even dream of today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 933760.0,
      "end_time": 937496.0,
      "text": "but which our great-great-great-great- grandchildren might someday."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 937520.0,
      "end_time": 938736.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 938760.0,
      "end_time": 944280.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}